external_knowledge:
- "Extensive reach" refers to the number of anatomical locations and disease classes associated with a disease;
- "Spanning" means being linked to or affecting;
- "Disease classes" are categories or types of diseases, often represented by unique identifiers;
- "Anatomical locations" are specific parts or regions of the body.

sql:
SELECT location_label, location_description
FROM anatomical_locations
WHERE location_last_updated > '2023-01-01';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_obo_foundry_mappings
FROM disease_anatomy_map
WHERE mapping_source = 'OBO Foundry';

SELECT COUNT(location_id) 
FROM anatomical_locations 
WHERE location_match_property = 'http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label';

external_knowledge:
- "anatomical location" refers to specific parts of the body, such as the intestine or heart;
- "mapping" refers to the relationship between a disease and an anatomical location, indicating where the disease typically affects;
- "most frequently mapped" means the anatomical location that appears the most times for a given disease.
